Medicine Information and Alternatives Lookup System 💊

This project is a Python-based tool that allows users to input a medicine name and receive a description of the medicine along with possible alternatives. It uses CSV data to store information about medicines, and retrieves the relevant details based on user input.

🔍 Features:
Takes user input for the medicine name.
Searches for and returns the medicine's description from a CSV file.
Lists alternative medicines (if available).
Provides clear and concise outputs for ease of use.

💻 Technologies Used:
Python: Main programming language used for scripting and logic implementation.
CSV: Used for storing and retrieving the dataset of medicines and their alternatives.
Input processing: Captures user input for the medicine search.
Data lookup: Looks up the relevant medicine information from the CSV file.

🚀 How to Use:
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/medicine-info-lookup.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd medicine-info-lookup
Install any required dependencies (if applicable):
bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the Python script:
bash
Copy code
python medicine_lookup.py
Enter the name of a medicine when prompted, and the system will display its description and similar alternatives.

📂 CSV Format:
The CSV file should have the following columns:
name: The name of the medicine.
description: A brief description of the medicine.
similar_medicines: A comma-separated list of alternative medicines.

Enter the medicine name: paracetamol
Description:
Paracetamol is a medication used to treat pain and reduce fever.

Similar medicines:
aspirin, ibuprofen
